    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Fuel System - Removal - Fuel System Tubing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="m3" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Fuel System Tubing</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the air inlet duct. See "Dual Turbocharger Assembly".</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3900007" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figN11/N11007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel system tubing and connections</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 16 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter to right cylinder head tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Secondary fuel filter housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter to left cylinder head tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel supply to filter tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel return to tank tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 16 bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 banjo bolt with check valve (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not smoke and keep fuel away from flames and sparks.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a suitable container under the secondary fuel filter housing to catch draining fuel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the Engine Fuel Pressure (EFP) switch, installed in the bottom of secondary fuel
                filter housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove secondary fuel filter cap to allow air into filter housing so fuel will drain.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After fuel has drained, install EFP switch into filter housing and tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges390_208.xml" xrefid="E30013B">special torque
                    <xref refid="E30013B"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M6 x 16 bolt securing the fuel return and fuel supply tubes to the oil pan.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M10 x 16 bolt securing the fuel return and fuel supply tubes to the left cylinder
                head.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M6 x 16 bolt securing the right fuel supply tube to the intake manifold.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove each M12 banjo bolt securing right and left fuel supply tubes to each cylinder head.
                Discard copper washers.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3001306" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figN11/N11012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Secondary fuel filter tubes and housing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel return to HFCM tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel supply to filter tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Fuel Pressure (EFP) switch</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter to left cylinder head tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter to right cylinder head tube</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove hollow screw from fuel supply to filter tube and discard copper washers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect fuel return to HFCM tube from fuel filter housing. Discard fitting O-ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect fuel filter to left and right cylinder head tubes from fuel filter housing.
                Discard fitting O-rings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove fuel tubes from engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cap all open ports on the secondary fuel filter housing using the
                <hotlnk document="eges390_209.xml" xrefid="E30013C">Cap Kit (all)</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="E30013C"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
